</TD></TR><TR><TD align="left" class="gpotbl_cell" scope="row"><E T="02">Note:</E> For VA purposes, an incapacitating episode is a period of acute symptoms severe enough to require prescribed bed rest and treatment by a physician or other healthcare provider.
